{"meta":{"category_id":"head_of_ai_uae","category_name":"Head of AI — UAE","macro_family":"ai_leadership","priority":"primary_target","confidence":"high","representation_proxy_mode":true},"overall_assessment":{"combined_fit_score":7.47,"readiness_tier":"GOOD","one_sentence_verdict":"Good baseline fit when positioned as an architect-first AI platform leader with delivery, reliability, governance, and stakeholder translation; still a stretch for literal executive Head of AI framing.","uncertainty_note":"Category evidence is strong but title noise is high, and the current master-CV view is proxy-derived rather than a canonical artifact; candidate fit is materially stronger for architect/player-coach AI leadership than for formal executive scope.","citations":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","Blueprint: Solutions Architect 20/35 (57.1%), AI Architect 7/35 (20.0%), IC 22/35 (62.9%), player-coach 8/35 (22.9%), budget/P&L 0/35 (0.0%)."]},"score_breakdown":{"candidate_evidence_coverage_score":8.1,"evidence_curation_completeness_score":6.9,"master_cv_representation_quality_score":6.8,"ai_architecture_fit_score":8.4,"leadership_scope_fit_score":6.4,"impact_proof_strength_score":8.1,"weighted_score_explanation":["Coverage is strong because curated evidence already supports enterprise architecture, modernization, reliability, stakeholder translation, mentoring, and enterprise AI workflow delivery across Seven.One, Samdock, and AI projects.","Curation completeness is lower because architect-title evidence and some role-framing material remain upstream or insufficiently promoted into reusable metadata, especially the stronger architect-family title variants from the knowledge base.","Representation quality is adequate but not sharp for this category: the headline is generic, the summary is overly anchored on one modernization story, and the current project/skills emphasis overweights tooling relative to architecture, governance, and stakeholder advisory.","AI architecture fit is high because Commander-4 and Lantern prove workflow-based AI systems, evaluation, routing, guardrails, structured outputs, and operational readiness in production settings.","Leadership scope fit is moderate because player-coach leadership, mentoring, hiring participation, and stakeholder influence are supported, but formal executive authority, org-building scale, and budget ownership are not.","Impact proof is strong because the curated store contains measurable reliability, adoption, velocity, onboarding, and cost signals such as 75% incident reduction, 3 years zero downtime, 2,000 users, 42 plugins, 25% velocity improvement, and 25 production tenants."],"citations":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:54","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:71","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:88","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:27","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:94","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:7","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:268","Blueprint: platform design 35/35 (100.0%), governance valued evidence 13/20 (65.0%), delivery 18/20 (90.0%), reliability 15/20 (75.0%), budget/P&L 0/35 (0.0%)."]},"strongest_supported_signals":[{"signal":"Legacy modernization and enterprise architecture transformation in a high-scale production system","why_it_matters_for_category":"Directly matches the category's architect-first center of gravity around platform design, modernization, reliability, and maintainable distributed systems.","status":"supported_and_curated","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:54","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:88"],"citation":"Supported by Seven.One modernization, architectural runway, and DDD evidence at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28, :54, :88."},{"signal":"Operational readiness, observability, and reliability leadership","why_it_matters_for_category":"This market values systems that ship and stay stable; the candidate has explicit production reliability proof rather than abstract strategy language.","status":"supported_and_curated","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:71","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:163","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:10"],"citation":"Supported by 75% incident reduction and 3 years zero downtime, the OpenSearch observability pipeline, MTTR-focused monitoring, and Lantern observability at :28, :71, :163, and data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:10."},{"signal":"Production AI workflow platform design with governance, evaluation, and tool integration","why_it_matters_for_category":"This category prefers production AI architecture, guardrails, and workflow orchestration with clear operational controls.","status":"supported_and_curated","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:354","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9"],"citation":"Supported by Commander-4 platform lead, structured output/tool-calling architecture, semantic caching, and guardrail/eval bullets at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282, :332, :354 and data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8-9."},{"signal":"Stakeholder translation and architectural north-star setting","why_it_matters_for_category":"Customer and stakeholder-facing architecture advisory is a core requirement in this category's player-coach profile.","status":"supported_and_curated","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250","data/master-cv/roles/06_clary_icon.md:103"],"citation":"Supported by Seven.One north-star and stakeholder collaboration evidence plus earlier client delivery work at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123, :250 and data/master-cv/roles/06_clary_icon.md:103."},{"signal":"Player-coach leadership through mentoring, standards, and selective hiring scope","why_it_matters_for_category":"The category rewards technical leadership and mentoring more than large-org management claims.","status":"supported_and_curated","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:94","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:110"],"citation":"Supported by mentoring 10+ engineers, promotion of 3 leads, hiring-process leadership, Samdock team leadership, and apprenticeship mentoring at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182, :217 and data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:94, :110."},{"signal":"Transferable non-AI architecture substrate from event-driven SaaS and distributed systems","why_it_matters_for_category":"The category explicitly values non-AI architecture work when framed as the substrate for enterprise AI delivery.","status":"supported_and_curated","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:27","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:142","data/master-cv/roles/04_fortis.md:27"],"citation":"Supported by Samdock 0→1 event-sourced CRM architecture, stakeholder event storming, 10x growth runway, and Fortis microservices architecture at data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:27, :44, :142 and data/master-cv/roles/04_fortis.md:27."}],"gap_analysis":[{"signal":"Architect-family title proof in reusable metadata","gap_type":"supported_upstream_pending_curation","why_it_matters":"The category is safer when led by an architect-family title rather than a management-heavy or executive label.","current_state":"Current representation leads with 'Engineering Leader / Software Architect' and role title 'Technical Lead (Addressable TV)'; stronger architect-title variants exist upstream but are not yet promoted into reusable metadata.","safe_interpretation":"Architect-led scope is credible; 'Lead Software Engineer / Technical Architect' is supported upstream, but should be treated as pending curation until promoted with provenance.","recommended_action":"Promote the architect-family title variants from the knowledge base into data/master-cv/role_metadata.json and the Seven.One role metadata so downstream CV generation can safely lead with architect framing.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:7","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:98","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:268","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:360"],"citation":"Not yet curated from docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:7, :98, :268, :360; current representation remains generic at data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3."},{"signal":"Stakeholder-facing architecture advisory and business translation","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"This category repeatedly rewards communication, collaboration, and stakeholder management tied to architecture decisions.","current_state":"Curated evidence exists for technical vision, stakeholder collaboration, event storming, and direct client communication, but the current summary and priority view largely foreground modernization and technical stack details.","safe_interpretation":"Claim technical stakeholder translation, architecture advisory, and cross-functional decision influence; avoid broader commercial or sales-ownership claims.","recommended_action":"Surface stakeholder-facing architecture evidence earlier in summary/profile and role prioritization, especially Seven.One stakeholder collaboration and Samdock event-storming facilitation.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/roles/06_clary_icon.md:103","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3"],"citation":"Underrepresented in the current representation despite curated support at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123, :250, data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44, and data/master-cv/roles/06_clary_icon.md:103."},{"signal":"Governance, guardrails, evaluation, and safe-production AI controls","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"Governance and evaluation readiness are category differentiators for architect-first AI leadership roles.","current_state":"Curated AI evidence includes guardrail profiles, per-silo policy enforcement, structured outputs, access control, retrieval evaluation, semantic caching, and eval-driven quality gates, but the current headline/summary do not foreground these differentiators.","safe_interpretation":"Claim production AI governance mechanisms, guardrails, evaluation harnesses, and safe structured-output architecture; avoid unsupported claims of enterprise-wide compliance ownership.","recommended_action":"Move governance/evaluation language into the summary and experience surface area ahead of framework inventories; preserve concrete mechanisms and avoid generic 'responsible AI' phrasing.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:354","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3"],"citation":"Supported by curated Commander-4 and Lantern controls at data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8-9, data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9, and data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332, :354, but not surfaced in data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3."},{"signal":"Reusable standards, reference patterns, and architecture enablement","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"Reusable standards and shared patterns are useful differentiators for this market's architect/player-coach roles.","current_state":"Curated evidence exists for DDD standards, ubiquitous language, architectural reviews, reusable component standards, and reusable server/template patterns, but this theme is not prominent in the current master-CV representation.","safe_interpretation":"Claim engineering standards, reusable patterns, and architecture enablement where tied to concrete systems and outcomes.","recommended_action":"Surface DDD standards, onboarding/velocity gains, and reusable pattern creation as architecture-enablement proof rather than burying them behind generic leadership phrasing.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:88","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:60","data/master-cv/roles/05_osram.md:74"],"citation":"Supported by standards and reusable-asset evidence at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:88, data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:60, and data/master-cv/roles/05_osram.md:74."},{"signal":"Enterprise multi-cloud architecture leadership","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"The category likes multi-cloud judgment, but overclaiming here would inflate the evidence beyond what is currently proven.","current_state":"Curated delivery shows AWS-heavy architecture, prior GCP experience, and multi-provider LLM endpoint routing, but not a clearly evidenced enterprise multi-cloud platform architecture mandate.","safe_interpretation":"Claim AWS architecture, prior GCP exposure, and multi-provider LLM routing; do not claim broad multi-cloud platform leadership as a headline identity.","recommended_action":"Keep cloud language precise and delivery-backed unless additional direct multi-cloud architecture evidence is curated.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:142","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7"],"citation":"Unsafe because the current evidence is AWS-led with some GCP and multi-provider routing signals, but not explicit enterprise multi-cloud ownership at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28, data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:142, and data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7."},{"signal":"Formal Head of AI or executive org-wide AI authority","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"Using the literal category title without executive scope proof would misrepresent the candidate's current evidence base.","current_state":"The evidence supports technical leadership, platform lead scope, mentoring, and selective hiring involvement, but does not prove department-wide AI leadership, budget ownership, or broad org-building authority.","safe_interpretation":"Position as architect-first AI platform leader or technical lead with delivery influence, not as formal executive Head of AI.","recommended_action":"Avoid executive title inflation until direct evidence exists for line ownership, org-building, and budget accountability.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3"],"citation":"Unsafe because current evidence shows player-coach and platform-lead scope, not executive ownership, at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182, :217, :282 and data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3."},{"signal":"AI compliance or audit ownership beyond concrete implemented controls","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"The category values governance, but unsupported expansion from GDPR product work into AI or enterprise compliance ownership would create unnecessary risk.","current_state":"Curated evidence supports GDPR/TCF delivery in ad-tech and guardrail/eval mechanisms in AI workflows, but not end-to-end AI compliance-program ownership.","safe_interpretation":"Claim implemented compliance-sensitive architecture and AI guardrails; avoid claiming enterprise AI audit, policy, or regulatory ownership.","recommended_action":"Keep governance wording concrete and mechanism-based unless broader ownership is curated with provenance.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:106","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9"],"citation":"Unsafe because the evidence supports GDPR/TCF execution and AI guardrails, not broad AI compliance ownership, at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:106 and data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8-9."}],"safe_claims_now":{"headline_safe":["Technical Lead / Software Architect | Enterprise AI Workflow Platforms | Distributed Systems, Reliability, Delivery","Software Architect | Event-Driven Platform Modernization | AI Workflows, Governance, Operational Readiness","Engineering Leader / Software Architect | Enterprise Platform Architecture | Stakeholder Translation, Reliability, Delivery"],"profile_safe":["Architect-first technical leader with 11 years of experience translating ambiguous platform and AI requirements into production systems, modernization roadmaps, and reliable delivery.","Designed and modernized distributed platforms across ad-tech and SaaS, including event-driven microservices, observability pipelines, DDD-based architecture standards, and enterprise AI workflow systems.","Built production AI capabilities around retrieval quality, structured outputs, guardrails, access control, semantic caching, and evaluation harnesses for reliable deployment.","Leads through technical vision, mentoring, cross-functional alignment, and architecture decision-making rather than formal executive org ownership."],"experience_safe":["Transformed a fragile legacy ad-tech platform into event-driven TypeScript microservices on AWS, reducing incidents by 75% and sustaining 3 years of zero downtime while continuing feature delivery.","Architected observability, monitoring, and incident-response capabilities, including an OpenSearch pipeline processing billions of events daily and proactive alerting workflows that reduced MTTR.","Led Commander-4 platform engineering for an enterprise AI workflow platform serving 2,000 users with 42 plugins, including hybrid retrieval, structured outputs, guardrails, access control, and semantic caching.","Architected a 0→1 event-sourced CRM platform using CQRS and EventStore, launching to production with 25 tenants and building growth runway for 10x scale.","Introduced DDD and bounded-context standards that cut onboarding from 6 months to 3 months, improved team velocity by 25%, and reduced requirement misalignment by 40%."],"leadership_safe":["Mentored 10+ engineers on architecture and cloud patterns and supported promotion of 3 engineers into lead roles.","Led technical hiring activities including selection criteria, interview strategy, and technical assessment design.","Facilitated stakeholder-facing architecture work through technical vision, event storming, subject-matter advisory, and transparent risk communication."],"unsafe_or_too_weak":["Head of AI, VP AI, Chief AI Officer, or Director of AI as a literal title claim.","Company-wide AI strategy ownership, enterprise-wide AI governance ownership, or department-level AI org leadership.","Budget/P&L accountability, large-scale org building, or formal performance management ownership at executive scope.","Broad enterprise multi-cloud leadership as a headline claim.","AI compliance-program, audit, or regulatory ownership beyond concrete controls and product-specific GDPR/TCF implementation."],"citations":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:71","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:88","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:106","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:163","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:354","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:27","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:142","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","Blueprint: title inflation risks and management leadership weakness; budget/P&L 0/35 (0.0%)."]},"representation_diagnosis":{"well_represented_now":["The current representation already surfaces flagship Seven.One modernization, architectural runway, observability, and DDD evidence tied to quantifiable outcomes.","The current project layer does show real AI platform delivery through Commander-4 and Lantern, including retrieval, routing, caching, and evaluation themes.","The existing summary anchors the profile in architecture and delivery, which is directionally correct for this category."],"underrepresented_now":["Architect-family title positioning is weaker than the underlying evidence base because the current headline is generic and the stronger architect-title variants remain upstream.","Stakeholder-facing advisory, business translation, and subject-matter-expert signals are not surfaced with enough prominence for this category.","Governance, guardrails, structured outputs, evaluation, and safe-production AI controls are present in curated project evidence but not elevated in the current summary/headline.","Player-coach leadership is present, but the representation does not cleanly distinguish it from management-heavy leadership language.","Transferable architecture depth from Samdock and earlier distributed-systems roles is underweighted relative to tool-centric AI skills."],"overstated_risk_now":["'Engineering Leader' in the current headline can read more management-heavy than the actual evidence warrants for this category.","The skills-priority layer leans heavily into RAG and tooling names, which risks obscuring the stronger architecture, reliability, and governance signals.","Because the representation is proxy-derived, the current summary may overfit one flagship modernization story and understate the candidate's broader architecture portfolio."],"representation_priorities":["Reframe the headline toward architect-first AI/platform leadership using current safe titles and architecture language.","Rewrite the summary so it balances modernization, operational readiness, stakeholder translation, and production AI governance rather than relying on a single legacy-transformation paragraph.","Reorder project emphasis to foreground platform scope, guardrails, evaluation, reliability, and operational readiness before tool inventories.","Bring forward one stakeholder-facing architecture bullet and one AI governance/control bullet into the top role/project surfaces.","Use Samdock 0→1 architecture evidence as a secondary proof block to broaden the candidate beyond one employer and show transferable platform design depth."],"citations":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:54","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:71","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:88","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:7","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:268"]},"curation_priorities":[{"priority_rank":1,"action":"Promote the Seven.One architect-family title variants into reusable metadata, including 'Lead Software Engineer / Technical Architect' alongside the current Technical Lead framing.","why_now":"This is the highest-leverage curation action because the category is title-sensitive in an architect-first way, and the stronger architect framing already exists upstream with high-confidence provenance.","target_files":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json"],"source_refs":["docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:7","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:98","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:268","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:360"],"expected_category_impact":"Improves headline safety, ATS alignment, and category fit without inventing executive scope.","citation":"High-confidence upstream title evidence is available at docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:7, :98, :268, :360."},{"priority_rank":2,"action":"Promote stakeholder-translation and architecture-advisory evidence from Seven.One into summary-ready metadata, especially SME collaboration, business-metric realization, and risk communication.","why_now":"Stakeholder translation is a category table-stakes signal, and the current representation under-surfaces it despite existing curated support.","target_files":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md"],"source_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:266","docs/current/achievement-review-tracker.yaml:49"],"expected_category_impact":"Strengthens architect/advisory positioning and reduces dependence on purely technical modernization framing.","citation":"Underlying curated evidence exists at data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123, :250, :266; tracker ref docs/current/achievement-review-tracker.yaml:49 is prioritization only."},{"priority_rank":3,"action":"Promote the AI governance and safe-production mechanisms from Commander-4/Lantern into top-level reusable summary/project metadata.","why_now":"These are category differentiators already supported by curated evidence, but they are not yet carrying enough weight in the master-CV representation.","target_files":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md"],"source_refs":["data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:354"],"expected_category_impact":"Raises differentiation on governance, guardrails, evaluation readiness, and production AI maturity.","citation":"Curated governance/control evidence is already present at data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8-9, data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9, and data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332, :354."},{"priority_rank":4,"action":"Broaden the